-- Hong Kong main index closes at highest since May 2008   
-- By Grace Li
-- Mon Aug 25, 2014 04:09AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 25 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's benchmark index finished at a new more-than-six-year high on Monday, reversing midday losses as financial and energy companies strengthened on corporate earnings.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> rose 0.2 percent to 25,166.91 points, its highest close since May 21, 2008. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong added 0.5 percent. Chinese oil firms were key outperformers, lifted by a 36 percent rise in second-quarter profit by Sinopec Corp <0386.HK>, which climbed 4.3 percent. [ID:nL4N0QS3BW] CNOOC <0883.HK> gained 1.2 percent and PetroChina <0857.HK> 0.9 percent. Some other H-shares were also boosted by good earnings. Sinopharm Group <1099.HK>, China's largest drug distributor, rose 3.3 percent to a 17-month closing high.